    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "mining: add always_add_coinbase_commitment option",
    "user": {
      "login": "Sjors",
      "id": 10217,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMjE3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10217?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/Sjors",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Sjors/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "Previously the `CoinbaseTx` returned by the Mining IPC interface always included the witness field and SegWit OP_RETURN output. This is unnecessary for empty blocks, and for blocks without any SegWit spends.\r\n\r\nThis PR omits them for blocks with SegWit spends, but gives clients the option to keep them. RPC behavior is unchanged.\r\n\r\nStrictly speaking it's a breaking change for <= v31 IPC clients, because they can't opt out of the new behavior. The interface is experimental so this is fine in general. Afaik clients don't rely on it, but I should double check that.\r\n\r\nBuilds on #35392. If we decide to drop that PR, then commit `mining: default coinbase commitment option off` might as well be squashed into `mining: add always_add_coinbase_commitment option`. It's currently done in two steps to better illustrate the \"breaking\" change.\r\n\r\nTwo alternatives are worth considering:\r\n1. Always omit them for IPC clients, don't expose `always_add_coinbase_commitment` (it's still needed internally for the RPC exception)\r\n2. Keep the current behavior of always adding these fields; empty blocks don't need the space savings",
